LETTER XXXII. (A'r'r. v. 20)

1. Saturnalibus. The Satumalia were at this time cele- brated Dec. 1749: the first day of the Satwrmlia is here indicated3 the siege therefore began on October 21. It must be remembered that before the Roman Calendar was reformed by Caesar in 45 the number of days in the month were: in March, May, July‚ October, 31 ; in Feb. 28 ; in all the rest 29. Remembering this, and allowing for inclusive reckoning‚ we find that the 67th day before Dec. 17 is Oct. 21.
